# Git Assignment - DmytroBolokhonov
a. What is an issue?
An issue is a way to track tasks, enhancements, bugs, or any other to-do items within a repository. It allows project members to discuss and collaborate on these topics.
b. What is a pull request?
A pull request is a way to propose changes to a repository. It allows collaborators to review the changes, discuss them, and approve or request modifications before the changes are merged into the main branch.
